{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f3cc5b15-34d7-45c3-8cdd-c3a5e17f63ab","content":"The template looks mostly well-formed but has a few issues before it's ready to publish:\n\n**Missing required/recommended fields:**\n\n1. **`$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation support.\n2. **`groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet template packs so multiple versions resolve correctly.\n3. **`precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the template coexist.\n4. **`preferNameDirectory`** — Typically `true` for project templates.\n\n**Other concerns:**\n\n- **`sourceName`** should match the root namespace/project filename in your template content — verify `MyWebApi.csproj` exists.\n- **`Framework` symbol** isn't wired to anything (e.g., a `replaces` or conditional in a `.csproj`). Without that, selecting a framework won't actually change the output.\n- No **`description`** field — NuGet Gallery and `dotnet new search` will show it blank.\n\n**Verdict:** Not quite ready. At minimum, add `$schema`, `groupIdentity`, and `description`, and ensure the `Framework` parameter actually replaces the `<TargetFramework>` value in your project file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2949095d-c80e-406c-b2a7-c15713cfdcbe","outputTokens":292,"requestId":"1C14:37A86A:AD674C2:BC2502C:69FD3562"},"id":"d75fc2a8-9da1-493f-9064-832eb9f68d8d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:59:24.327Z","parentId":"7997261c-323f-40ac-bc17-827ec2d30d27"}
